<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a restricted area of occupancy (AOO = 12 km2) and should be preliminarily assessed as Endangered [(EN) B2ab (iii)], following the 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" publicationUrl="https://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" refId="B8" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. https://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14." url="https://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuideLines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
guidelines. Only the populations in Cata Altas are protected since it occurs inside the Reserva 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Patrimônio">Patrimonio</normalizedToken>
Natural 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Santuário">Santuario</normalizedToken>
do 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Caraça">Caraca</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Flowers have been collected in April and from July to September and fruits from July to October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
The specific epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">Microlicia deflexa</taxonomicName>
&quot; refers to the sepal characteristically deflexed on flower and immature fruit i.e. turned abruptly downwards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. serpyllifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpyllifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. serpyllifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.Don, which occurs in Rio de Janeiro, Minas Gerais, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
, Bahia and Distrito Federal (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860200859401" author="Silva, MAO" journalOrPublisher="Rodriguesia" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="609 - 647" refId="B21" refString="Silva, MAO, Romero, R, 2008. Melastomataceae das serras do municipio de Delfinopolis, Minas Gerais, Brasil. Rodriguesia 59 (4): 609 - 647, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860200859401" title="Melastomataceae das serras do municipio de Delfinopolis, Minas Gerais, Brasil." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860200859401" volume="59" year="2008">Silva and Romero 2008</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. fulva" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Romero, R" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" publicationUrl="http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/jabot/floradobrasil/FB9782" refId="B19" refString="Romero, R, Woodgyer, EM, 2015. Microlicia: Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/jabot/floradobrasil/FB9782" title="Microlicia: Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro." url="http://floradobrasil.jbrj.gov.br/jabot/floradobrasil/FB9782" year="2015">Romero and Woodgyer 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Romero, R" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" publicationUrl="http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" refId="B20" refString="Romero, R, Fontelas, JC, Moreira, KVC, Ferreira-Alves, R, Oliveira, LFA, Versiane, AFA, 2020. Microlicia. Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" title="Microlicia. Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro." url="http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" year="2020">Romero et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) in campo rupestre, campo limpo and cerrado. Both species have long pedicel and sepal, dimorphic stamen with bicolorous and tetrasporangiate anther. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia serpyllifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpyllifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia serpyllifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a very peculiar velutinous indumentum composed of thin, short and soft trichomes covering branch, leaf, pedicel, hypanthium and sepal mixed with spherical glands (vs. glandular indumentum mixed with spherical, golden glands in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The sepal in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. serpyllifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpyllifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. serpyllifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is triangular and ascending (vs. linear-lanceolate and deflexed). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also bears some resemblance to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia helvola" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helvola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia helvola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Spreng.) Triana, which occurs in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
, Mato Grosso do Sul, Mato Grosso and Minas Gerais States (
<bibRefCitation author="Romero, R" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" publicationUrl="http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" refId="B20" refString="Romero, R, Fontelas, JC, Moreira, KVC, Ferreira-Alves, R, Oliveira, LFA, Versiane, AFA, 2020. Microlicia. Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" title="Microlicia. Flora do Brasil 2020. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro." url="http://reflora.jbrj.gov.br/reflora/floradobrasil/FB9782" year="2020">Romero et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.455.1.2" author="Versiane, AFA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="9 - 20" refId="B26" refString="Versiane, AFA, Silva, DN, Romero, R, 2020. A new species of Microlicia (Melastomataceae) from Bolivia and Brazil, a new synonym, and an identification key for the genus in Mato Grosso, Brazil. Phytotaxa 455 (1): 9 - 20, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.455.1.2" title="A new species of Microlicia (Melastomataceae) from Bolivia and Brazil, a new synonym, and an identification key for the genus in Mato Grosso, Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.455.1.2" volume="455" year="2020">Versiane et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) in campo limpo, campo sujo and the edges of vereda and swamp areas (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" author="Bacci, LF" journalOrPublisher="Hoehnea" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="541 - 556" refId="B2" refString="Bacci, LF, Versiane, AFA, Oliveira, ALF, Romero, R, 2016. Melastomataceae na RPPN do Clube Caca e Pesca Itororo, Uberlandia, MG, Brasil. Hoehnea 43 (4): 541 - 556, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" title="Melastomataceae na RPPN do Clube Caca e Pesca Itororo, Uberlandia, MG, Brasil." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" volume="43" year="2016">Bacci et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860201667314" author="Versiane, AFA" journalOrPublisher="Feddes Repertorium" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" refId="B25" refString="Versiane, AFA, Santos, ML, Romero, R, 2016. Melastomataceae na Serra dos Pirineus, Goias, Brasil. Rodriguesia 67: 721-759. https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860201667314" title="Melastomataceae na Serra dos Pirineus, Goias, Brasil. Rodriguesia 67: 721 - 759." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/2175-7860201667314" year="2016">Versiane et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and less frequently in cerrado rupestre (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.450.1.3" author="Machado, AIMR" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="17 - 54" refId="B10" refString="Machado, AIMR, Romero, R, 2020. Melastomataceae in the Parque Estadual da Serra Dourada, Goias state, Brazil. Phytotaxa 450 (1): 17 - 54, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.450.1.3" title="Melastomataceae in the Parque Estadual da Serra Dourada, Goias state, Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.450.1.3" volume="450" year="2020">Machado and Romero 2020</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. helvola" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helvola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. helvola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are subshrub or shrub with sessile leaf or with a short petiole, acute at the apex, rounded at the base and 3-5-veined. Furthermore, both species have pinkish petal and dimorphic stamens with bicolorous anthers. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. helvola" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helvola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. helvola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having an indumentum of setose trichomes mixed with spherical glands (vs. glandular trichomes mixed with spherical glands in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), urceolate and 10-striate hypanthium (vs. cylindrical and not striate), sepal shorter than the hypanthium length (vs. sepal longer than the hypanthium length) and polysporangiate anther (vs. tetraesporangiate). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Romero &amp; Valentim" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Microlicia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microlicia deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Microlicia deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also resembles 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phlogiformis" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlogiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. phlogiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Versiane &amp; R.Romero, which also occurs in the Clube 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Caça">Caca</normalizedToken>
e Pesca 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Itororó">Itororo</normalizedToken>
de 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Uberlândia">Uberlandia</normalizedToken>
, in campo 
<normalizedToken originalValue="úmido">umido</normalizedToken>
or inside the vereda on waterlogged soil (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" author="Bacci, LF" journalOrPublisher="Hoehnea" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" pagination="541 - 556" refId="B2" refString="Bacci, LF, Versiane, AFA, Oliveira, ALF, Romero, R, 2016. Melastomataceae na RPPN do Clube Caca e Pesca Itororo, Uberlandia, MG, Brasil. Hoehnea 43 (4): 541 - 556, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" title="Melastomataceae na RPPN do Clube Caca e Pesca Itororo, Uberlandia, MG, Brasil." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/2236-8906-27/2016" volume="43" year="2016">Bacci et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The indumentum, the sepals and the long pedicel of both species are similar; however, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phlogiformis" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlogiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. phlogiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having flowers in dichasia (vs. solitary) and ascending sepals (vs. deflexed). Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Comparative features between Microlicia deflexa and relatives." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/09DC64E4DB5DB9E74AE0F5C04B69A81E" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" tableUuid="09DC64E4DB5DB9E74AE0F5C04B69A81E">1</tableCitation>
includes additional features comparing 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. helvola" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helvola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. helvola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. phlogiformis" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phlogiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. phlogiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. serpyllifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serpyllifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. serpyllifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="M." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. deflexa" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">M. deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
